commit.title: Go back to using sets for Constraints.
commit.message:
Go back to using sets for Constraints.

The temporary Tree solution wasn't very aesthetically nice.
It also meant carrying around extra constraints, since duplicates
weren't eliminated by virtue of being a set.
This then closes #11.
